summary:
Above from today’s (5/11/2018) very in depth Adam Driver interview on vulture.com.
I’m sorry. But if this isn’t the best...
body:
Above from today’s (5/11/2018) very in depth Adam Driver interview on vulture.com.

I’m sorry. But if this isn’t the best evidence that Bendemption is going to happen I don’t know what is.

I can’t imagine a scenario where an actor like Adam would have said yes to this life changing (for the worse it sounds like for him right now) role just for an ‘oh then in EpIX he is all evil again and Rey kills him’ ending.

Adam Driver on His Most Important Work and Why He’s Not Actually “Intense”

blog.title: Miit'alor
blog.description: I am a descriptivist linguist for the Mando'a language. I show what it can do, not what it MUST do. This is a place for discussion about Mando'a, and Mandalorian society and culture. Feel free to use the head cannons from this blog (or reblogged from others) in your RP or writing. All words and descriptions are taken from the mandoa.org Mandalorian Dictionary. Want to support this blog? Buy me a Kofi? OR buy some Mando'a themed items? Visit our Discord? Blog icon by Rina
